HEADWORD: Salutiferous
<hw>Sal`u*tif"er*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>salutifer</ets>; <ets>salus</ets>, <ets>-utis</ets>, health +
<ets>ferre</ets> to bring.]</ety> <def>Bringing health; healthy;
salutary; beneficial; <as>as, <ex>salutiferous</ex> air</as>.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Innumerable powers, all of them <qex>salutiferous</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Cudworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Healthful; healthy; salutary;
salubrious.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Salutiferously</ent>⟦br⟧
